For similar formulas, see the Ramanujan–Sato series.

== Failure to classify elliptic curves over other fields ==
The formula_55-invariant is only sensitive to isomorphism classes of elliptic curves over the complex numbers, or more generally, an algebraically closed field. Over other fields there exist examples of elliptic curves whose formula_55-invariant is the same, but are non-isomorphic. For example, let formula_57 be the elliptic curves associated to the polynomialsformula_58both having formula_55-invariant formula_60. Then, the rational points of formula_61 can be computed as:formula_62since formula_63 There are no rational solutions with formula_64. This can be shown using Cardano&#x27;s formula to show that in that case the solutions to formula_65 are all irrational. 

On the other hand, on the set of pointsformula_66 the equation for formula_67 becomes formula_68. Dividing by formula_69 to eliminate the formula_70 solution, the quadratic formula gives the rational solutions: formula_71If these curves are considered over formula_72, there is an isomorphism formula_73 sendingformula_74

